basics.label: Mechanical Engineering Intern
basics.summary: Highly motivated mechanical engineering student (EIT) interested in pursuing an engaging position in the corporate setting. A dedicated student with problem-solving, leadership, and communication skills along with the capability to build relationships and work in a team-oriented environment.

work.name: Company Name
work.summary: Worked with a team of four to build a mobile robot in UCSD's MAE 3 class. Evaluated robot parts and estimated energy transfer. Used AutoCAD to develop drawings and implement them into the Lasercamm (Laser Cutter). Acted as an Academic Employee (Grader) for UCSD's MAE 105.

work.name: Company Name
work.summary: Operations of crystallization robotics and compound management. Assisted daily order fulfillment using research compounds. Prepared stock solutions.

Academic mentoring of third grade students at El Toyon Elementary. Assisted the children with academic support and moral encouragement.
